-- Angola Plans to Repay $6.8 Billion Construction Debt, Radio Ecclesia Says
-- Candido Mendes
-- 2010-07-19T11:22:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/angola-plans-to-repay-6-8-billion-construction-debt-radio-ecclesia-says.html

          
          
             Angola will start repaying its $6.8
billion debt to construction companies, Radio Ecclesia reported,
citing President Jose Eduardo dos Santos.  
 The country will pay small and medium sized building
companies withing two months while bigger companies will receive
40 percent of what they are owed in that period and the rest in
instalments over the next one to two years, the Luanda-based
radion station said, citing dos Santos.  
 Dos Santos spoke after meeting with Portuguese President
Anibal Cavaco Silva.  
